    <item>
      <title>Healing pets generates aggro now.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=333862#M333862</link>
      <description>I first saw this in the bug thread and went to test it myself, healing pets now generates aggro. Healing pets has not generated aggro in several years, I believe the original reason had something to do with clerics getting eaten due to the gobs of extra aggro they nabbed by shooting off group heals with pets around. The effect of this nerf (if it was intentional) or bug (if it was not) will be as follows:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Pets as a whole will be banned from many group/raid situations, not for lame reasons like (the way overblown) pet push, but for fully justifiable reasons like "they're killing the cleric".&lt;br&gt;2. The cleric/druid/shaman + magician druids are no longer viable.&lt;br&gt;3 The only method of add control that magicians have, simply healing the pet while two mobs beat on it and hoping for the best, is no longer viable. Magicians are one of the worst high-powered solo classes when it comes to adds. We have no way to pull singles anymore, and we have nothing to do to stop adds once they're aggroed. The magician's only option is to run, gate, or throw whatever they can on their pet and hope it survives against 2/3 mobs. With this change, the magician will heal his pet when the add aggros, and immediately get summoned and destroyed, this is a huge nerf to magician solo power, and the absolute opposite of what we've been hoping for (some way to deal with adds, preferably a pet that can distract them).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Numbers 1 and 3 are the ones I'm particularly concerned about. I'm pretty sure we were told that the devs knew about this and were not going to change it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is not in the magician section and should not be moved to the magician section because it affects all pet classes to some extent or another, I just personally believe it detriments magicians the most.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
