      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Just a note on pet as a tank.&amp;nbsp; Soloing it works well, or duo with a healer.&amp;nbsp; And full pet groups can do some incredible damage.&amp;nbsp; That said, a pet cannot compete with a real tank at most levels.&amp;nbsp; I am a mid end raider (Anguish/DP guild) and have an Anguish level pet focus.&amp;nbsp; As such my Air pet well buffed/equipped probably is around 16-17k hp (and earth if I used it could probably get above 20k).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When I group however, its usually with non raiders.&amp;nbsp; And who do we use as a tank?&amp;nbsp; My ranger friend with about 9.3k hp unbuffed (around 12.7k raid buffed I think).&amp;nbsp; Even as just a chain class, he mitigates so much better than my pet its rediculous.&amp;nbsp; And generates far more aggro.&amp;nbsp; And is able to back off from the mob if a heal is running late to give it time (smarter tank).&amp;nbsp; Should he go down my pet can usually hold its own ok for a bit, but the amount of heals required to keep it up compared to the ranger makes this a very mana consuming process.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So I don't picture Pets taking the place of real tanks anytime soon.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
