&lt;P&gt;"However I can't say on a raid, yes he can have a pet, but no you can't because you're too stupid to control it.'&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;You sure can, and you sure should.&amp;nbsp;Well&amp;nbsp;maybe&amp;nbsp;don't use the word "stupid," but you can say "Your pet is causing problems,&amp;nbsp;please suspend."&amp;nbsp; See how easy that is?&amp;nbsp; Of course, you have to be aware enough to know which pet and which owner caused the problem, but if you don't, you have no business giving these kinds of instructions till you know exactly what happened anyway.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Personally I expect people to not have to have their hand held to play their class, but if they are still new and really can't play it well yet, I don't offend everyone to avoid offending them.&amp;nbsp; I tell them exactly what they're doing wrong, and exactly what they need to do differently.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If being &lt;STRONG&gt;taught&lt;/STRONG&gt; offends them,&amp;nbsp;I say "Go now, don't let the door hit you on the way out."&amp;nbsp; If you don't play your class right, you get to be told how to play it.&amp;nbsp; You talk to the person you need to talk to, not to everyone in general.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Worried about offending the poor player by targeting the communication to the one responsible?&amp;nbsp;Don't be.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Instead, worry about offending all the others who play well.&amp;nbsp; They should not be offended because they've done nothing to warrant this kind of treatment.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;On that note, can we&amp;nbsp;stop saying "KILL PETS"&amp;nbsp; on raids (who thought that up?).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;You say "Suspend pets," "Pets off," or "Hold pets."&amp;nbsp; Its not rocket science, its easy, try it.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The&amp;nbsp;ubiquitous insulting of pet classes (saying KILL PETS as if they're bad is offensive, for example)&amp;nbsp;is a holdover from when mostly kids played this game, imo--back then, rude talk was the norm, pet classes being one of the accepted targets for it.&amp;nbsp; Rudeness is juvenile, get it?&amp;nbsp; Pet classes can be good players, and I expect them to be--if they are not, that person who doesn't play well plays without a pet--JUST them.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;And pet push is extreme once you get all your flurry AAs, etc.&amp;nbsp; It is a problem, and you don't run around in a raid to position your pet, you miss group heals that way, for example.&amp;nbsp; And there are many solutions that have been suggested,&amp;nbsp;one or more of which&amp;nbsp;need to be implemented. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
